1.title: Meet the Syndicates
1.plot: Three separate horse owning groups that are competing for fame, glory, and money! Donkey Island the flush with cash team, Great Friends led by the charismatic Skott Kapalan, and the Flying Phillies, Del Mar's first ever all female run syndicate.

2.title: And They're Off
2.plot: It's opening day at one of the most famous horse racing tracks in the world. Each get's into the action right away, making side bets that have nothing to do with the track - or do they? The Fillies have an opening day contender, can they start with a win or are they to focused on fashion?

3.title: Three Teams One Win
3.plot: Donkey Island head Jeff Strauss has made a weight bet to loose 30 pounds over the course of the season. Selma makes good in the kitchen. Donkey Island has a contender in the race and the girls get some wisdom from a living legend Joe Harper. Screaming Eagle wine anyone, it's on Jeff!

4.title: Where the Surf Meets the Turf
4.plot: Water sports competition with all three syndicates show off the physical side of each group. Also the Fillies get to collect some winnings. Craig Dado has to keep his investors positive as they question the season start.

5.title: Rivalry
5.plot: The competition is increasing, and the side bets as well. Scott Kaplan, throws out a side bet that involves jumping off a cliff. A volley ball tournament adds some bragging rights, and a charity dinner helps everyone blow off some steam. We also meet Jennifer Wayne and Caroline Hobby whom are considering joing the Fillies, but Scott Kaplan has other plans.

6.title: Around the Bend
6.plot: Jennifer Wayne gets to hear some stories about her grandfather "John Wayne" from living legend Joe Harper. Another shot at glory for Great Friends. See how the sacrifice of Dave Martinez a Del Mar employee saved the life of a small child from a fire and watch how the Del Mar family rallies around one of their best. Jeff gets an interesting lesson in his "personal life".

7.title: By a Length
7.plot: Jennifer and Caroline bring the house down at Del Mar with the national anthem. A food truck fair, may not be a good idea for Scott Kaplan. The girls are treated by Scott Kaplan with an all expense paid trip to South beach - sort of.

8.title: We Won!
8.plot: Who has won, well the season is over, and the side bets are as well, with a little boxing match to end any doubt. Plus get a re-cap on the season and see who surprised everyone!

imdb.plot outline: The world of horse racing heats up in the beautiful beach town of Del Mar, CA where rival syndicates battle for supremacy. The women have invaded and they're competing, they're winning,and they're conquering this "Sport of Kings". It's man against woman, brother against sister, and husband against wife. Watch summer days turn to summer nights, and playful wagers turn to heated fights, after the money pours and champagne flows, family ties will be tested, allegiances will be divided, and a winner will be crowned. Each week we follow the horse racing industry's largest characters as they train champion thoroughbreds, acquire investors, and embody the overall extravagance of the Del Mar lifestyle. This docu-series showcases the unique competition of horse racing syndicates and the lives they lead on and off the track. A group of beautiful people, marred by massive egos, and family rivalries, packaged into three dynamic syndicates- it's winner take all.
imdb.title: Stable Wars: Del Mar
plot: Three rival horse racing syndicates battle as financial, social, and sexual conflicts explode to redefine this Sport of Kings- it's all about winning.::Anonymous
